LASSA FEVER - GERMANY EX NIGERIA
********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
See Also
Lassa fever: background 20000325001055
[1
Date: 4 Apr 2000
From: Wolfgang Preiser <w.preiser@em.uni-frankfurt.de>
Source: Hessian Broadcasting Station (Hessischer Rundfunk), Frankfurt am
Main, Germany

PATIENT DIED OF LASSA FEVER
---------------------------
In a Wiesbaden (town near Frankfurt am Main, capital of Hesse) hospital a
57-year old Nigerian man died of Lassa fever last Saturday [1 Apr 2000.
According to information released by the Social Ministry, the highly
contagious virus was discovered only today. The brain of the patient had
been infected, but the virus had not been detectable in the blood.
The Nigerian man had been admitted to the Horst Schmidt Hospital in
Wiesbaden on 27 Mar 2000for diagnostic purposes. All contacts have been
traced according to the ministry and precautions have been instigated. The
risk of infection was low in this case.
--
Dr. med. Wolfgang Preiser, DTM&H, DipRCPath
